      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "A fast, lightly-defended cargo fit. Initial is buy-only; A-rated is the trade baseline with a bi-weave shield; Engineered maximises laden range, speed and protected tonnage. Run the hardpoints clean unless a route is genuinely hostile.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Speed and range, not bulk",
            "text": "The Phantom can't out-haul a freighter, so play to its strengths: A-rated thrusters and a long FSD to chain distant markets and run from interdictions. A bi-weave shield in one class-5 slot costs ~32t of cargo but keeps you alive long enough to high-wake. Strip the shield for ~190t on safe lanes; keep it for contested ones."
          },
          "notes": {
            "MediumHardpoint1": "Optional gimballed pulse as a cheap deterrent; Efficient keeps it cool and low-draw. Leave empty to save mass on safe lanes.",
            "MediumHardpoint2": "Second deterrent pulse, same Efficient roll — token defence only; the Phantom's real defence is running.",
            "TinyHardpoint1": "First shield booster; Heavy Duty multiplies the bi-weave's raw MJ so you survive long enough to high-wake.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Second Heavy-Duty booster — the cheapest large gain in shield strength.",
            "TinyHardpoint3": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and Thermal-Vent resets.",
            "TinyHardpoint4": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds chaff salvos. Chaff spoils gimballed and turreted fire.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rate for headroom; Low Emissions runs cool and quiet and Thermal Spread bleeds the heat — useful when smuggling.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rated + Dirty Drives keep the laden speed that outruns interdictions.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "A-rate this FIRST — laden range is the Phantom's trade edge; Increased Range + Mass Manager maximise the jump.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass; Lightweight trims more — life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "A-rated; Engine Focused + Super Conduits feed the sustained boost you need to flee.",
            "Radar": "Drop to D and go Lightweight; a hauler needs no sensor range, so save the mass.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock C tank; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size6": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot02_Size5": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot03_Size5": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot04_Size5": "Bi-weave in one class-5 slot — fast regen, Reinforced + Hi-Cap for MJ; costs ~32t of cargo but buys survival. Swap for a rack on safe lanes.",
            "Slot05_Size3": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot06_Size3": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot07_Size3": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
